🚀 DOCKER — ZERO TO HERO (REAL-TIME NOTES)
🧠 1. WHAT IS DOCKER?

👉 Problem:

“It works on my machine but not in server”

👉 Solution:

Docker packages application + dependencies into a container

🎤 Interview Answer

“Docker is a containerization platform that enables packaging applications and dependencies into lightweight, portable containers ensuring consistency across environments.”

🧱 2. DOCKER ARCHITECTURE
Client → Docker Daemon → Containers
Docker CLI → commands
Docker Daemon → runs containers
Registry → stores images
📦 3. IMAGE vs CONTAINER
Image	Container
Blueprint	Running instance
Read-only	Executable
🎤 Answer

“Image is a template, container is a running instance of that image.”

🧾 4. DOCKERFILE (VERY IMPORTANT)

👉 Used to build image

🔥 Real Dockerfile (Production Level)
FROM python:3.9-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 5000
CMD ["python", "app.py"]
🧠 KEY CONCEPTS
FROM → base image
WORKDIR → working directory
COPY → copy files
RUN → install dependencies
CMD → start app
🎤 Answer

“Dockerfile contains instructions to build Docker images in a layered approach.”

🧱 5. DOCKER LAYERS

👉 Each command = layer

👉 Benefit:

Faster builds
Caching
🌐 6. PORT MAPPING
docker run -p 5000:5000 app

👉 Host → Container

🔐 7. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
🔹 Pass env variables
docker run -e ENV=prod app
🔹 In Dockerfile
ENV ENV=prod
🎤 Answer

“Environment variables are used to configure applications dynamically without hardcoding values.”

📂 8. VOLUMES (DATA PERSISTENCE)
docker run -v /host:/container app

👉 Data persists even if container stops

🌐 9. NETWORKING
Containers communicate via networks
Default: bridge
⚙️ 10. IMPORTANT COMMANDS (REAL-TIME)
🔹 Build
docker build -t app:v1 .
🔹 Run
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 app:v1
🔹 List
docker ps
docker ps -a
🔹 Logs
docker logs <id>
🔹 Exec
docker exec -it <id> bash
🔹 Stop
docker stop <id>
🔹 Remove
docker rm <id>
docker rmi <image>
🐞 11. DEBUGGING (VERY IMPORTANT)
🔹 Scenario:

👉 App not working

🔥 Steps:
docker ps
docker logs <id>
docker exec -it <id> bash
🎤 Answer

“I debug container issues using docker logs, exec into the container, and verify application logs and dependencies.”

🏷️ 12. IMAGE TAGGING (PRODUCTION)
docker tag app:v1 gcr.io/project/app:v1

👉 Used for:

Versioning
Rollback
☁️ 13. PUSH TO REGISTRY
docker push gcr.io/project/app:v1
🎤 Answer

“We tag Docker images with version or commit ID and push them to container registries like GCR or ECR.”

🔁 14. DOCKER IN CI/CD (REAL-TIME)
Pipeline:
GitHub → Jenkins → Docker build → Push → Deploy
Jenkins runs:
docker build
docker push
🎤 Answer

“Docker is integrated into CI/CD pipelines to build and deploy containerized applications automatically.”

⚡ 15. BEST PRACTICES

👉 Use:

Small base image (slim/alpine)
.dockerignore
Version tagging (not latest)
Multi-stage builds (advanced)
🔐 16. SECURITY

👉 Avoid:

Hardcoded secrets
Root user
